{
  "texts": [
    "This impact suggests that, with proper guidance, ChatGPT can go beyond being a mere automation tool and become an active pedagogical assistant that enhances the quality of students' critical thinking.However, in the area of source usage, the study reveals a significant limitation of ChatGPT compared to traditional methods, aligning with previous research highlighting AI models' inability to critically evaluate the relevance and quality of sources.",
    "Nevertheless, this study provides an innovative analysis by showing that this weakness is not only technical but also pedagogical, as the manual process of searching for and evaluating sources is an integral part of the development of research competencies.",
    "Therefore, while ChatGPT can be a powerful tool for improving certain aspects of research, it cannot replace the essential skills students need to develop for managing academic sources effectively.Another innovative contribution of this study is that, although ChatGPT enhances aspects related to coherence and originality, it does not guarantee greater content depth or a significant improvement in solving complex problems.",
    "This finding is relevant because it highlights that while ChatGPT is efficient for generating quick, structured ideas, its ability to foster deep critical analysis is limited.",
    "Unlike previous studies that promote AI as a comprehensive solution for learning, this study offers a nuanced perspective: ChatGPT can be a valuable complement, but it does not replace the intensive cognitive processes required by traditional methods, which are essential for the formation of well-rounded researchers."
  ]
}